The article provides the latest information on the US government's response to the earthquake disaster in Haiti. It states that the US has mobilized resources and personnel for relief efforts, with the goal of saving lives and preventing further catastrophe. The government is coordinating with the United Nations and other countries to provide aid and water quickly throughout Haiti. The article highlights various measures taken by the government, including the deployment of military personnel to support humanitarian efforts, the arrival of the USNS Comfort hospital ship, and the distribution of medical supplies. It also mentions the coordination of evacuation and rescue operations, the provision of food and water, and efforts to reunite families and address the needs of vulnerable children. The article concludes by providing ways for people to contribute to relief efforts and obtain information about loved ones in Haiti.